author: Justin Harp
title: TV show ratings: Once Upon a Time stays strong on Sunday against NBC's football - Once Upon a Time Cult
text: NBC won the key 18-49 demographic on Sunday (October 11) with 5.0, according to Nielsen figures.Sunday Night Football reeled in 5.8 (16.13m) at 8.30pm on the Peacock Network. Â© ABC / Jack Rowand Once Upon a Time remained strong with 1.6 (5.22m) at 8pm on ABC.Later in the night, ABC's Blood & Oil fell four-tenths of a point at 9pm with 0.8 (3.82m) and Quantico took 1.6 (5.67m) at 10pm.Fox's lineup saw the recently-renewed Bob's Burgers earn 1.0 (2.24m) at 7.30pm, The Simpsons appeal to 1.5 (3.29m) at 8pm, Brooklyn Nine-Nine garner 1.3 (2.73m) at 8.30pm, Family Guy dip to 1.4 (2.83m) at 9pm, and The Last Man On Earth fall four-tenths with 1.1 (2.67m) at 9.30pm.A football delay on CBS led 60 Minutes to reach 3.0 (15.24m) at 7.30pm, Madam Secretary to generate 1.4 (10.93m) at 8.30pm, The Good Wife to attract just 1.1 (8.46m) at 9pm, and CSI: Cyber to pull in 0.9 (6.2m) at 9.30pm.
